{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JsbCqYj3CkxwQH8FXBcJ5c","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Backflow\n     2→\n     3→Background agent orchestrator that runs Claude Code in ephemeral Docker containers on AWS EC2 spot instances. POST a task (repo + prompt), get back a branch with commits and optionally a PR.\n     4→\n     5→## Prerequisites\n     6→\n     7→- Go 1.24+\n     8→- AWS CLI (configured with credentials)\n     9→- Docker\n    10→- `sqlite3` CLI (for `make db-status`)\n    11→\n    12→## Local Development\n    13→\n    14→### Setup\n    15→\n    16→```bash\n    17→cp .env.example .env\n    18→# Edit .env — at minimum set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY and GITHUB_TOKEN\n    19→```\n    20→\n    21→For local-only development without AWS, set `BACKFLOW_MODE=local` in `.env`. This skips EC2 provisioning and runs containers on the local Docker daemon.\n    22→\n    23→### Build and Run\n    24→\n    25→```bash\n    26→make build          # Compile to bin/backflow\n    27→make run            # Build + run (auto-sources .env)\n    28→```\n    29→\n    30→Server starts on `http://localhost:8080`. The orchestrator poll loop and HTTP server run as concurrent goroutines.\n    31→\n    32→### Testing\n    33→\n    34→```bash\n    35→make test           # Run all tests (no cache)\n    36→make lint           # go vet\n    37→\n    38→# Run a single test\n    39→go test ./internal/store/ -run TestCreateTask -v\n    40→\n    41→# Run tests for a specific package\n    42→go test ./internal/api/ -v -count=1\n    43→```\n    44→\n    45→Tests create temporary SQLite databases that are cleaned up automatically. No external services needed.\n    46→\n    47→### Build the Agent Image Locally\n    48→\n    49→```bash\n    50→make docker-build-local    # Single-arch build, no push\n    51→```\n    52→\n    53→## Database\n    54→\n    55→Backflow uses SQLite in WAL mode. The database file location is configured via `BACKFLOW_DB_PATH` (default: `backflow.db` in the working directory).\n    56→\n    57→### Schema\n    58→\n    59→Two tables: `tasks` and `instances`. See `internal/store/sqlite.go` for the full schema.\n    60→\n    61→### Migrations\n    62→\n    63→There are no separate migration files. Schema is managed in `internal/store/sqlite.go` in the `migrate()` method. All DDL uses `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` and `CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS`, so it's safe to run on every startup.\n    64→\n    65→**To add a new column:**\n    66→\n    67→1. Add an `ALTER TABLE ... ADD COLUMN` statement to `migrate()` in `internal/store/sqlite.go`, wrapped in an idempotent check (SQLite will error if the column already exists, so ignore the error or check `pragma table_info` first).\n    68→2. Update the `INSERT`, `UPDATE`, and `SELECT` statements in the same file.\n    69→3. Update the model struct in `internal/models/`.\n    70→\n    71→**To inspect the database:**\n    72→\n    73→```bash\n    74→make db-status                              # Dump all tasks and instances\n    75→sqlite3 backflow.db \".schema\"               # Show schema\n    76→sqlite3 backflow.db \"SELECT id, status, created_at FROM tasks ORDER BY created_at DESC LIMIT 10;\"\n    77→```\n    78→\n    79→**To reset the database:** delete the `backflow.db` file. It will be recreated on next startup.\n    80→\n    81→## AWS Setup (EC2 Mode)\n    82→\n    83→### One-Time Infrastructure\n    84→\n    85→```bash\n    86→make setup-aws\n    87→```\n    88→\n    89→This creates: ECR repo, IAM role, security group, and launch template. Copy the `BACKFLOW_LAUNCH_TEMPLATE_ID` from the output into `.env`.\n    90→\n    91→### Deploy Agent Image\n    92→\n    93→```bash\n    94→make docker-deploy\n    95→# If docker needs sudo: make docker-deploy DOCKER=\"sudo docker\"\n    96→```\n    97→\n    98→Builds a multi-arch image (amd64 + arm64) and pushes to ECR.\n    99→\n   100→## Submitting Tasks\n   101→\n   102→```bash\n   103→# Simple task\n   104→./scripts/create-task.sh https://github.com/org/repo \"Fix the login bug\"\n   105→\n   106→# With PR creation\n   107→./scripts/create-task.sh https://github.com/org/repo \"Fix the login bug\" --pr\n   108→\n   109→# Full options\n   110→./scripts/create-task.sh https://github.com/org/repo \"Add unit tests\" \\\n   111→  --pr --pr-title \"Add tests\" \\\n   112→  --budget 15 --model claude-sonnet-4-6 \\\n   113→  --branch my-feature --target-branch develop \\\n   114→  --context \"Focus on the auth module\" \\\n   115→  --claude-md \"Always use table-driven tests\" \\\n   116→  --env \"GOPRIVATE=github.com/org/*\"\n   117→```\n   118→\n   119→Or call the API directly:\n   120→\n   121→```bash\n   122→curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/tasks \\\n   123→  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n   124→  -d '{\"repo_url\": \"https://github.com/org/repo\", \"prompt\": \"Fix the bug\", \"create_pr\": true}'\n   125→```\n   126→\n   127→## Monitoring and Operations\n   128→\n   129→```bash\n   130→# Database state\n   131→make db-status\n   132→\n   133→# Task details\n   134→curl http://localhost:8080/api/v1/tasks/{id}\n   135→\n   136→# Container logs\n   137→curl http://localhost:8080/api/v1/tasks/{id}/logs?tail=100\n   138→\n   139→# Health check\n   140→curl http://localhost:8080/api/v1/health\n   141→\n   142→# Shell into an agent EC2 instance\n   143→aws ssm start-session --target i-0abc...\n   144→```\n   145→\n   146→### Task Lifecycle\n   147→\n   148→`pending` → `provisioning` → `running` → `completed` | `failed` | `interrupted` | `cancelled`\n   149→\n   150→### Instance Lifecycle\n   151→\n   152→`pending` → `running` → idle 5 min → `terminated`. Spot interruptions automatically re-queue affected tasks.\n   153→\n   154→## API Reference\n   155→\n   156→| Method | Path | Description |\n   157→|--------|------|-------------|\n   158→| `POST` | `/api/v1/tasks` | Create a task |\n   159→| `GET` | `/api/v1/tasks` | List tasks (`?status=`, `?limit=`, `?offset=`) |\n   160→| `GET` | `/api/v1/tasks/{id}` | Get task details |\n   161→| `DELETE` | `/api/v1/tasks/{id}` | Cancel a task |\n   162→| `GET` | `/api/v1/tasks/{id}/logs` | Container logs (`?tail=100`) |\n   163→| `GET` | `/api/v1/health` | Health check |\n   164→\n   165→## Auth Modes\n   166→\n   167→- **`api_key`** (default) — Uses Anthropic API key. Supports multiple concurrent agents. Pay per token.\n   168→- **`max_subscription`** — Uses Claude Max subscription credentials. One agent at a time. Flat rate.\n   169→\n   170→## Webhooks\n   171→\n   172→Set `BACKFLOW_WEBHOOK_URL` in `.env`:\n   173→\n   174→```json\n   175→{\n   176→  \"event\": \"task.completed\",\n   177→  \"task_id\": \"bf_01KK...\",\n   178→  \"repo_url\": \"https://github.com/org/repo\",\n   179→  \"prompt\": \"Fix the bug\",\n   180→  \"message\": \"\",\n   181→  \"agent_log_tail\": \"last 20 lines...\",\n   182→  \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-13T22:00:00Z\"\n   183→}\n   184→```\n   185→\n   186→Events: `task.created`, `task.running`, `task.completed`, `task.failed`, `task.needs_input`, `task.interrupted`\n   187→\n   188→Filter with `BACKFLOW_WEBHOOK_EVENTS=task.completed,task.failed`.\n   189→\n   190→## Configuration\n   191→\n   192→All config is via environment variables (or `.env` file).\n   193→\n   194→| Variable | Default | Description |\n   195→|----------|---------|-------------|\n   196→| `BACKFLOW_MODE` | `ec2` | `ec2` or `local` |\n   197→| `BACKFLOW_AUTH_MODE` | `api_key` | `api_key` or `max_subscription` |\n   198→| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | | Required for `api_key` mode |\n   199→| `CLAUDE_CREDENTIALS_PATH` | | Path to `~/.claude/` for `max_subscription` mode |\n   200→| `GITHUB_TOKEN` | | For cloning private repos and creating PRs |\n   201→| `BACKFLOW_LISTEN_ADDR` | `:8080` | Server listen address |\n   202→| `BACKFLOW_DB_PATH` | `backflow.db` | SQLite database path |\n   203→| `AWS_REGION` | `us-east-1` | AWS region |\n   204→| `BACKFLOW_INSTANCE_TYPE` | `t4g.medium` | EC2 instance type |\n   205→| `BACKFLOW_LAUNCH_TEMPLATE_ID` | | From `make setup-aws` |\n   206→| `BACKFLOW_MAX_INSTANCES` | `5` | Max EC2 instances |\n   207→| `BACKFLOW_CONTAINERS_PER_INSTANCE` | `4` | Containers per instance |\n   208→| `BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_MODEL` | `claude-sonnet-4-6` | Default Claude model |\n   209→| `BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_MAX_BUDGET` | `10` | Default budget (USD) |\n   210→| `BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_MAX_RUNTIME_MIN` | `30` | Default max runtime (min) |\n   211→| `BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_MAX_TURNS` | `200` | Default max turns |\n   212→| `BACKFLOW_WEBHOOK_URL` | | Webhook endpoint |\n   213→| `BACKFLOW_WEBHOOK_EVENTS` | all | Comma-separated event filter |\n   214→| `BACKFLOW_POLL_INTERVAL_SEC` | `5` | Orchestrator poll interval (sec) |\n   215→| `DOCKER` | `docker` | Docker command (e.g. `sudo docker`) |\n   216→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01PDcBuJDkTbrVDZqqd8XFxc","session_id":"8cc67d88-77a2-42c6-8a46-47b1ddf8c38f","uuid":"22a4c58f-3ee4-4858-ac5e-89fd120d0595"}
