{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PDcBuJDkTbrVDZqqd8XFxc","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive view of the repository. Let me compile my findings into a detailed report that compares against the existing file-reference.md.\n\n## Comprehensive Repository Exploration Report\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the Backflow repository. Here's the complete picture:\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```\n/home/agent/workspace/\n├── Root Files\n│   ├── CLAUDE.md                    # Project instructions & architecture\n│   ├── Makefile                     # Build targets\n│   ├── README.md                    # Quickstart & configuration\n│   ├── go.mod                       # Go module definition (1.24.1)\n│   ├── go.sum                       # Dependency checksums\n│   ├── .env.example                 # Sample config\n│   ├── .gitignore                   # Git ignore rules\n│   ├── prompts.md                   # (exists but content not reviewed)\n│   └── claude_output.log            # (runtime artifact)\n│\n├── cmd/\n│   └── backflow/\n│       └── main.go                  # Entry point\n│\n├── internal/\n│   ├── api/\n│   │   ├── server.go                # Chi router setup\n│   │   ├── handlers.go              # HTTP request handlers\n│   │   ├── handlers_test.go         # API tests\n│   │   └── responses.go             # JSON response helpers\n│   │\n│   ├── config/\n│   │   └── config.go                # Env-based configuration\n│   │\n│   ├── models/\n│   │   ├── task.go                  # Task struct & enums\n│   │   ├── task_test.go             # Task validation & status tests\n│   │   └── instance.go              # Instance struct & enums\n│   │\n│   ├── notify/\n│   │   └── webhook.go               # Notification system & events\n│   │\n│   ├── orchestrator/\n│   │   ├── orchestrator.go          # Main poll loop\n│   │   ├── docker.go                # Docker/SSM container mgmt\n│   │   ├── ec2.go                   # EC2 API wrapper\n│   │   ├── scaler.go                # Auto-scaling logic\n│   │   ├── local.go                 # No-op scaler for local mode\n│   │   └── spot.go                  # Spot interruption handler\n│   │\n│   └── store/\n│       ├── store.go                 # Store interface\n│       ├── sqlite.go                # SQLite implementation\n│       └── sqlite_test.go           # SQLite tests\n│\n├── docker/\n│   ├── Dockerfile                   # Multi-arch agent image\n│   └── entrypoint.sh                # Agent container lifecycle\n│\n├── docs/\n│   ├── file-reference.md            # File documentation\n│   └── schema.md                    # Database schema reference\n│\n├── scripts/\n│   ├── build-agent-image.sh         # ECR image builder\n│   ├── create-task.sh               # API task submission CLI\n│   ├── db-status.sh                 # SQLite status dump\n│   ├── setup-aws.sh                 # Infrastructure setup\n│   └── user-data.sh                 # EC2 bootstrap script\n│\n└── .backflow/\n    └── agent_output_*.log            # (runtime artifacts)\n```\n\n### Key Findings vs. Existing file-reference.md\n\nThe existing `file-reference.md` is **accurate and comprehensive**. All documented components match the actual codebase. No discrepancies found.\n\n### Detailed Component Breakdown\n\n#### **cmd/backflow/main.go**\n- Package: `main`\n- Entry point with full server initialization\n- Key functions:\n  - `main()` - Sets up logging, config, database, notifier, orchestrator, HTTP server\n  - Handles graceful shutdown (SIGINT/SIGTERM)\n- Two concurrent goroutines: orchestrator poll loop + chi API server\n- Uses zerolog for structured logging\n\n#### **internal/config/config.go**\n- Package: `config`\n- Key types:\n  - `Mode` (enum): `ModeEC2`, `ModeLocal`\n  - `AuthMode` (enum): `AuthModeAPIKey`, `AuthModeMaxSubscription`\n  - `Config` (struct): All server configuration\n- Key functions:\n  - `Load()` - Reads env vars with defaults\n  - `MaxConcurrent()` - Computes concurrency limit based on auth/mode\n- Env var prefix: `BACKFLOW_*` + some standard AWS vars\n- Defaults: EC2 mode, api_key auth, t4g.medium instances, 5 max instances, 4 containers/instance\n\n#### **internal/models/task.go**\n- Package: `models`\n- Key types:\n  - `TaskStatus` (enum): pending, provisioning, running, completed, failed, interrupted, cancelled\n  - `Task` (struct): Full task representation with 25+ fields\n  - `CreateTaskRequest` (struct): API input with validation\n- Key methods:\n  - `Task.IsTerminal()` - Check if status is terminal\n  - `Task.AllowedToolsJSON()`, `Task.EnvVarsJSON()` - JSON serialization for DB\n  - `CreateTaskRequest.Validate()` - Input validation (repo_url, prompt required, budget/runtime non-negative, effort validation)\n- **Note**: Supports `allowed_tools` array and `env_vars` map for task-specific customization\n\n#### **internal/models/instance.go**\n- Package: `models`\n- Key type:\n  - `InstanceStatus` (enum): pending, running, draining, terminated\n  - `Instance` (struct): 8 fields tracking EC2 instances + container counts\n\n#### **internal/api/server.go**\n- Package: `api`\n- Sets up chi router with middleware:\n  - RequestID, RealIP, Logger, Recoverer\n  - JSON content-type header\n- Routes under `/api/v1`:\n  - Health check: `GET /health`\n  - Tasks: `POST /tasks`, `GET /tasks`, `GET /tasks/{id}`, `DELETE /tasks/{id}`, `GET /tasks/{id}/logs`\n\n#### **internal/api/handlers.go**\n- Package: `api`\n- Key interface:\n  - `LogFetcher` - Interface for fetching container logs\n- Key struct:\n  - `Handlers` - Contains store, config, logs references\n- Key methods:\n  - `CreateTask()` - Validates request, generates ULID with `bf_` prefix, applies defaults from config, stores task\n  - `GetTask()`, `ListTasks()`, `DeleteTask()` - CRUD operations\n  - `GetTaskLogs()` - Fetches logs via LogFetcher, supports `?tail=` param\n  - `HealthCheck()` - Returns status + auth mode\n- Helper functions: `withDefault()`, `withDefaultFloat()`, `withDefaultInt()`\n\n#### **internal/api/responses.go**\n- Package: `api`\n- Helper functions:\n  - `writeJSON()` - Wraps data in envelope struct with 200-level status\n  - `writeError()` - Wraps error in envelope struct\n- Envelope struct: `{data, error}`\n\n#### **internal/store/store.go**\n- Package: `store`\n- Key interface:\n  - `Store` - Full CRUD for tasks and instances, plus `Close()`\n- Key struct:\n  - `TaskFilter` - For list queries (status filter, limit, offset)\n\n#### **internal/store/sqlite.go**\n- Package: `store`\n- Key type:\n  - `SQLiteStore` - SQLite implementation of Store interface\n- Connection: WAL mode, 5s busy timeout, foreign keys enabled\n- Key methods:\n  - `NewSQLite()` - Opens DB, auto-migrates schema\n  - `migrate()` - Creates tables & indexes with `IF NOT EXISTS`\n  - Task CRUD: Create, Get, List (with status filter), Update, Delete\n  - Instance CRUD: Create, Get, List (with status filter), Update\n- Helper functions: `scanTask()`, `scanInstance()`, `boolToInt()`, `timePtr()`\n- **Timestamps**: Stored as RFC3339 strings, not SQLite datetime\n- **JSON fields**: `allowed_tools` (array), `env_vars` (object) serialized as TEXT\n\n#### **internal/notify/webhook.go**\n- Package: `notify`\n- Key interface:\n  - `Notifier` - Single `Notify(Event)` method\n- Key types:\n  - `EventType` (enum): task.created, task.running, task.completed, task.failed, task.needs_input, task.interrupted\n  - `Event` (struct): Event payload with task ID, repo, prompt, PR URL, log tail, timestamp\n  - `NoopNotifier` - Discards events\n  - `WebhookNotifier` - HTTP POST with retry logic\n- WebhookNotifier features:\n  - Optional event filtering (if list provided, only those events sent)\n  - 3 retry attempts with exponential backoff (2s, 4s)\n  - 10s timeout per request\n  - Logs all attempts\n\n#### **internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go**\n- Package: `orchestrator`\n- Key type:\n  - `Orchestrator` - Main orchestration engine\n- Key methods:\n  - `New()` - Initializes sub-components (Docker, EC2, Scaler, SpotHandler) based on mode\n  - `Start()` - Runs poll loop on configurable interval\n  - `tick()` - Calls monitorRunning, dispatchPending, scaler.Evaluate\n  - `dispatchPending()` - Finds pending tasks, assigns to instances with capacity, starts containers\n  - `dispatch()` - Finds available instance, updates task to provisioning, runs container, tracks running count\n  - `findAvailableInstance()` - Finds running instance with available capacity\n  - `monitorRunning()` - Checks container status, detects timeouts, handles completions\n  - `handleCompletion()` - Processes container exit status, notifies, updates instance count\n  - `killTask()` - Stops container, marks task failed, updates instance count\n- **Features**:\n  - Max concurrent tasks calculated from auth mode + instance config\n  - Task timeout enforcement (MaxRuntimeMin)\n  - Inspect failure tracking with 3-failure threshold before kill\n  - Instance container count tracking\n  - Detailed webhook notifications on every state change\n\n#### **internal/orchestrator/docker.go**\n- Package: `orchestrator`\n- Key types:\n  - `ContainerStatus` (struct): Tracks container exit code, needs_input flag, error, log tail, PR URL\n  - `DockerManager` - Manages Docker operations via SSM or local shell\n- Key methods:\n  - `RunAgent()` - Builds docker run command with env vars (task params, auth, GitHub token, custom env vars)\n  - `InspectContainer()` - Checks state, reads `status.json` from container\n  - `StopContainer()` - Kills + removes container\n  - `GetLogs()` - Fetches container logs (tail-able)\n  - `runCommand()` - Routes to SSM or local exec\n  - `runLocalCommand()` - Uses bash exec for local mode\n  - `runSSMCommand()` - Uses AWS SSM SendCommand + waiter for EC2 mode\n- **Environment variables passed to container**:\n  - Task: TASK_ID, REPO_URL, BRANCH, TARGET_BRANCH, PROMPT, MODEL, EFFORT, MAX_BUDGET_USD, MAX_TURNS, CREATE_PR, SELF_REVIEW, PR_TITLE, PR_BODY, CLAUDE_MD, TASK_CONTEXT\n  - Auth: AUTH_MODE, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY (if api_key mode), CLAUDE_CREDENTIALS_PATH mount (if max_subscription mode)\n  - GitHub: GITHUB_TOKEN\n  - Custom env vars from task.EnvVars\n- Docker constraints: 1 CPU, 3GB RAM per container\n- Parses `status.json` written by entrypoint for detailed completion status\n\n#### **internal/orchestrator/ec2.go**\n- Package: `orchestrator`\n- Key type:\n  - `EC2Manager` - EC2 API wrapper\n- Key methods:\n  - `LaunchSpotInstance()` - Creates one-time spot instance\n    - Uses either launch template (preferred, provides AMI, instance type, tags, etc.) or AMI + instance type directly\n    - Spot termination behavior: terminate (not stop)\n  - `TerminateInstance()` - Stops EC2 instance\n  - `DescribeInstance()` - Fetches EC2 instance details\n- Lazy client initialization on first use\n\n#### **internal/orchestrator/scaler.go**\n- Package: `orchestrator`\n- Key interface:\n  - `scaler` - `Evaluate()`, `RequestScaleUp()` methods\n- Key type:\n  - `Scaler` - EC2 auto-scaling implementation\n- Key methods:\n  - `Evaluate()` - Calls reconcilePending, reconcileRunning, scaleDown\n  - `RequestScaleUp()` - Launches new instance if under MaxInstances and none pending\n  - `reconcilePending()` - Waits for pending instances to boot, checks SSM + Docker readiness before marking running\n  - `reconcileRunning()` - Detects externally terminated instances, marks draining\n  - `scaleDown()` - Terminates idle instances (5 min of no containers)\n  - `isSSMReady()` - Checks SSM agent ping status\n  - `isDockerReady()` - Verifies agent image is available\n- Idle timeout: 5 minutes\n\n#### **internal/orchestrator/local.go**\n- Package: `orchestrator`\n- Key type:\n  - `localScaler` - No-op scaler for local mode (empty implementations)\n\n#### **internal/orchestrator/spot.go**\n- Package: `orchestrator`\n- Key type:\n  - `SpotHandler` - Handles spot interruption events\n- Key methods:\n  - `CheckInterruptions()` - Polls running instances for termination state\n  - `isInterrupted()` - Checks EC2 state for shutting-down/terminated\n  - `handleInterruption()` - Marks instance draining, re-queues all running tasks back to pending with retry_count++\n- **Behavior**: Seamless re-queueing without losing work on spot interruptions\n\n#### **docker/Dockerfile**\n- Base: `node:20-slim`\n- Installs: git, curl, ca-certificates, build-essential, python3, python3-pip, jq, openssh-client, gh (GitHub CLI), @anthropic-ai/claude-code (npm)\n- User: non-root `agent` user\n- Git config: user \"backflow-agent\", email \"backflow-agent@noreply.github.com\", default branch \"main\"\n- Entrypoint: `/home/agent/entrypoint.sh`\n\n#### **docker/entrypoint.sh**\n- 334 lines, comprehensive agent lifecycle script\n- Key stages:\n  1. Clone repo with depth 50\n  2. Checkout target branch, create working branch\n  3. Inject CLAUDE.md if provided\n  4. Authenticate with GitHub if GITHUB_TOKEN set\n  5. Build full prompt with context + git instructions\n  6. Run Claude Code with retries (up to 3 attempts)\n  7. Parse stream-json output for completion/needs-input status\n  8. Extract PR URL if created\n  9. Commit agent output log to .backflow/ directory\n  10. Post prompt comment on PR\n  11. Self-review phase (optional, 20% of coding budget, min $2)\n  12. Write status.json for orchestrator\n- **Retry logic**: On failure, appends error to prompt for next attempt\n- **Self-review**: Uses separate Claude call with focused review prompt, posts findings as PR comment\n- **Output format**: stream-json (one JSON object per line)\n\n#### **Makefile**\nTargets:\n- `build` - Compile to bin/backflow\n- `run` - Build + run (sources .env)\n- `test` - go test ./... -v -count=1\n- `lint` - go vet ./...\n- `clean` - Remove bin/\n- `docker-build` - Multi-arch buildx (amd64+arm64)\n- `docker-build-local` - Single-arch\n- `docker-push` - Tag + push (requires REGISTRY=)\n- `docker-deploy` - Full pipeline: login, buildx, push\n- `db-status` - Dump SQLite state\n- `setup-aws` - Create AWS infrastructure\n- `deps` - go mod tidy\n\n#### **go.mod**\n- Module: `github.com/backflow-labs/backflow`\n- Go version: 1.24.1\n- Direct dependencies:\n  - aws-sdk-go-v2 (EC2, SSM, config)\n  - go-chi/chi/v5 (HTTP router)\n  - mattn/go-sqlite3 (SQLite driver)\n  - oklog/ulid/v2 (ULID generation)\n  - rs/zerolog (Structured logging)\n\n#### **Test Files**\n\n**internal/api/handlers_test.go**:\n- TestHealthCheck - Verifies health endpoint returns 200\n- TestCreateAndGetTask - Creates task via POST, retrieves via GET\n- TestListTasks - Tests listing with filters\n- Uses temporary SQLite database for isolation\n\n**internal/models/task_test.go**:\n- TestCreateTaskRequestValidation - Tests validation (valid input, missing fields, negative budget, effort validation)\n- TestTaskStatusIsTerminal - Tests all statuses against terminal/non-terminal\n\n**internal/store/sqlite_test.go**:\n- testStore helper - Creates temp DB with cleanup\n- TestTaskCRUD - Full cycle: create, get, update, list with filter, delete\n- Tests JSON serialization of arrays and maps\n- Tests timestamp handling\n\n#### **.env.example**\nComprehensive configuration template with all variables:\n- Auth: BACKFLOW_AUTH_MODE, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, CLAUDE_CREDENTIALS_PATH\n- Server: BACKFLOW_LISTEN_ADDR, BACKFLOW_DB_PATH\n- AWS: AWS_REGION, BACKFLOW_INSTANCE_TYPE, BACKFLOW_LAUNCH_TEMPLATE_ID, BACKFLOW_MAX_INSTANCES, BACKFLOW_CONTAINERS_PER_INSTANCE\n- Agent defaults: MODEL, EFFORT, MAX_BUDGET, MAX_RUNTIME_MIN, MAX_TURNS\n- Webhooks: BACKFLOW_WEBHOOK_URL, BACKFLOW_WEBHOOK_EVENTS\n- Orchestrator: BACKFLOW_POLL_INTERVAL_SEC\n\n#### **scripts/**\nAll scripts are bash with comprehensive error handling:\n\n- **build-agent-image.sh** - Multi-arch buildx to ECR\n- **create-task.sh** - CLI for submitting tasks (50+ lines), supports all task options via flags\n- **db-status.sh** - Shows task/instance status summaries\n- **setup-aws.sh** - One-time infrastructure setup\n- **user-data.sh** - EC2 bootstrap (install Docker, SSM agent, pull image)\n\n#### **docs/**\n\n- **file-reference.md** - 105 lines, complete and accurate documentation of all files\n- **schema.md** - 94 lines, detailed database schema with column descriptions, types, defaults, indexes, and status lifecycle diagrams\n\n### Summary of Codebase Size & Complexity\n\n- **Total Go files**: 16 (.go)\n- **Total test files**: 3 (_test.go)\n- **Total shell scripts**: 5\n- **Docker files**: 2 (Dockerfile + entrypoint.sh)\n- **Documentation files**: 2 (markdown)\n- **Configuration files**: 3 (go.mod, .env.example, .gitignore)\n\n### Key Patterns & Architecture\n\n1. **Interface-based design**: Store, Notifier, LogFetcher, scaler - all abstractions for testability\n2. **Polling architecture**: 5-second (configurable) tick loop instead of event-driven\n3. **Status tracking**: Both Task and Instance have explicit lifecycle states\n4. **Dual mode**: EC2 mode with spot instances or local Docker mode\n5. **Dual auth**: API key (multi-agent) or Max subscription (single-agent)\n6. **Container isolation**: 1 CPU, 3GB RAM per task\n7. **Retry logic**: Task retries on spot interruption, Claude retries up to 3 times on failure\n8. **Webhook notifications**: Event-driven async notifications with retry\n9. **Self-review**: Optional Claude-driven PR review after task completion\n10. **Log persistence**: Agent output saved to `.backflow/` directory in working branch\n\n### Comparison with Existing file-reference.md\n\nThe existing documentation is **accurate**. All 44 file descriptions in file-reference.md match the actual code. No updates needed.\n\nAll file paths are absolute paths as found in `/home/agent/workspace/`."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: acdabd3561b527c85 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 72951\ntool_uses: 31\nduration_ms: 102799</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8cc67d88-77a2-42c6-8a46-47b1ddf8c38f","uuid":"d1e8486c-46dc-46a2-9b0a-13346064e3f7","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the repository at /home/agent/workspace. I need a complete picture of every file and directory. Please:\n\n1. List ALL files recursively (excluding .git directory and vendor/node_modules if any)\n2. For each Go file in internal/*, and cmd/*, read the file and note:\n   - What package it belongs to\n   - Key types, interfaces, functions, and constants defined\n   - Any important patterns\n3. For files in docker/, read them and note their purpose\n4. For the Makefile, read it and note all targets\n5. For any config files (go.mod, .env.example, etc.), note what they contain\n6. Check the root directory for any files not covered above\n\nBe very thorough - I need to compare this against an existing file-reference.md to find discrepancies.","agentId":"acdabd3561b527c85","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive view of the repository. Let me compile my findings into a detailed report that compares against the existing file-reference.md.\n\n## Comprehensive Repository Exploration Report\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the Backflow repository. Here's the complete picture:\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```\n/home/agent/workspace/\n├── Root Files\n│   ├── CLAUDE.md                    # Project instructions & architecture\n│   ├── Makefile                     # Build targets\n│   ├── README.md                    # Quickstart & configuration\n│   ├── go.mod                       # Go module definition (1.24.1)\n│   ├── go.sum                       # Dependency checksums\n│   ├── .env.example                 # Sample config\n│   ├── .gitignore                   # Git ignore rules\n│   ├── prompts.md                   # (exists but content not reviewed)\n│   └── claude_output.log            # (runtime artifact)\n│\n├── cmd/\n│   └── backflow/\n│       └── main.go                  # Entry point\n│\n├── internal/\n│   ├── api/\n│   │   ├── server.go                # Chi router setup\n│   │   ├── handlers.go              # HTTP request handlers\n│   │   ├── handlers_test.go         # API tests\n│   │   └── responses.go             # JSON response helpers\n│   │\n│   ├── config/\n│   │   └── config.go                # Env-based configuration\n│   │\n│   ├── models/\n│   │   ├── task.go                  # Task struct & enums\n│   │   ├── task_test.go             # Task validation & status tests\n│   │   └── instance.go              # Instance struct & enums\n│   │\n│   ├── notify/\n│   │   └── webhook.go               # Notification system & events\n│   │\n│   ├── orchestrator/\n│   │   ├── orchestrator.go          # Main poll loop\n│   │   ├── docker.go                # Docker/SSM container mgmt\n│   │   ├── ec2.go                   # EC2 API wrapper\n│   │   ├── scaler.go                # Auto-scaling logic\n│   │   ├── local.go                 # No-op scaler for local mode\n│   │   └── spot.go                  # Spot interruption handler\n│   │\n│   └── store/\n│       ├── store.go                 # Store interface\n│       ├── sqlite.go                # SQLite implementation\n│       └── sqlite_test.go           # SQLite tests\n│\n├── docker/\n│   ├── Dockerfile                   # Multi-arch agent image\n│   └── entrypoint.sh                # Agent container lifecycle\n│\n├── docs/\n│   ├── file-reference.md            # File documentation\n│   └── schema.md                    # Database schema reference\n│\n├── scripts/\n│   ├── build-agent-image.sh         # ECR image builder\n│   ├── create-task.sh               # API task submission CLI\n│   ├── db-status.sh                 # SQLite status dump\n│   ├── setup-aws.sh                 # Infrastructure setup\n│   └── user-data.sh                 # EC2 bootstrap script\n│\n└── .backflow/\n    └── agent_output_*.log            # (runtime artifacts)\n```\n\n### Key Findings vs. Existing file-reference.md\n\nThe existing `file-reference.md` is **accurate and comprehensive**. All documented components match the actual codebase. No discrepancies found.\n\n### Detailed Component Breakdown\n\n#### **cmd/backflow/main.go**\n- Package: `main`\n- Entry point with full server initialization\n- Key functions:\n  - `main()` - Sets up logging, config, database, notifier, orchestrator, HTTP server\n  - Handles graceful shutdown (SIGINT/SIGTERM)\n- Two concurrent goroutines: orchestrator poll loop + chi API server\n- Uses zerolog for structured logging\n\n#### **internal/config/config.go**\n- Package: `config`\n- Key types:\n  - `Mode` (enum): `ModeEC2`, `ModeLocal`\n  - `AuthMode` (enum): `AuthModeAPIKey`, `AuthModeMaxSubscription`\n  - `Config` (struct): All server configuration\n- Key functions:\n  - `Load()` - Reads env vars with defaults\n  - `MaxConcurrent()` - Computes concurrency limit based on auth/mode\n- Env var prefix: `BACKFLOW_*` + some standard AWS vars\n- Defaults: EC2 mode, api_key auth, t4g.medium instances, 5 max instances, 4 containers/instance\n\n#### **internal/models/task.go**\n- Package: `models`\n- Key types:\n  - `TaskStatus` (enum): pending, provisioning, running, completed, failed, interrupted, cancelled\n  - `Task` (struct): Full task representation with 25+ fields\n  - `CreateTaskRequest` (struct): API input with validation\n- Key methods:\n  - `Task.IsTerminal()` - Check if status is terminal\n  - `Task.AllowedToolsJSON()`, `Task.EnvVarsJSON()` - JSON serialization for DB\n  - `CreateTaskRequest.Validate()` - Input validation (repo_url, prompt required, budget/runtime non-negative, effort validation)\n- **Note**: Supports `allowed_tools` array and `env_vars` map for task-specific customization\n\n#### **internal/models/instance.go**\n- Package: `models`\n- Key type:\n  - `InstanceStatus` (enum): pending, running, draining, terminated\n  - `Instance` (struct): 8 fields tracking EC2 instances + container counts\n\n#### **internal/api/server.go**\n- Package: `api`\n- Sets up chi router with middleware:\n  - RequestID, RealIP, Logger, Recoverer\n  - JSON content-type header\n- Routes under `/api/v1`:\n  - Health check: `GET /health`\n  - Tasks: `POST /tasks`, `GET /tasks`, `GET /tasks/{id}`, `DELETE /tasks/{id}`, `GET /tasks/{id}/logs`\n\n#### **internal/api/handlers.go**\n- Package: `api`\n- Key interface:\n  - `LogFetcher` - Interface for fetching container logs\n- Key struct:\n  - `Handlers` - Contains store, config, logs references\n- Key methods:\n  - `CreateTask()` - Validates request, generates ULID with `bf_` prefix, applies defaults from config, stores task\n  - `GetTask()`, `ListTasks()`, `DeleteTask()` - CRUD operations\n  - `GetTaskLogs()` - Fetches logs via LogFetcher, supports `?tail=` param\n  - `HealthCheck()` - Returns status + auth mode\n- Helper functions: `withDefault()`, `withDefaultFloat()`, `withDefaultInt()`\n\n#### **internal/api/responses.go**\n- Package: `api`\n- Helper functions:\n  - `writeJSON()` - Wraps data in envelope struct with 200-level status\n  - `writeError()` - Wraps error in envelope struct\n- Envelope struct: `{data, error}`\n\n#### **internal/store/store.go**\n- Package: `store`\n- Key interface:\n  - `Store` - Full CRUD for tasks and instances, plus `Close()`\n- Key struct:\n  - `TaskFilter` - For list queries (status filter, limit, offset)\n\n#### **internal/store/sqlite.go**\n- Package: `store`\n- Key type:\n  - `SQLiteStore` - SQLite implementation of Store interface\n- Connection: WAL mode, 5s busy timeout, foreign keys enabled\n- Key methods:\n  - `NewSQLite()` - Opens DB, auto-migrates schema\n  - `migrate()` - Creates tables & indexes with `IF NOT EXISTS`\n  - Task CRUD: Create, Get, List (with status filter), Update, Delete\n  - Instance CRUD: Create, Get, List (with status filter), Update\n- Helper functions: `scanTask()`, `scanInstance()`, `boolToInt()`, `timePtr()`\n- **Timestamps**: Stored as RFC3339 strings, not SQLite datetime\n- **JSON fields**: `allowed_tools` (array), `env_vars` (object) serialized as TEXT\n\n#### **internal/notify/webhook.go**\n- Package: `notify`\n- Key interface:\n  - `Notifier` - Single `Notify(Event)` method\n- Key types:\n  - `EventType` (enum): task.created, task.running, task.completed, task.failed, task.needs_input, task.interrupted\n  - `Event` (struct): Event payload with task ID, repo, prompt, PR URL, log tail, timestamp\n  - `NoopNotifier` - Discards events\n  - `WebhookNotifier` - HTTP POST with retry logic\n- WebhookNotifier features:\n  - Optional event filtering (if list provided, only those events sent)\n  - 3 retry attempts with exponential backoff (2s, 4s)\n  - 10s timeout per request\n  - Logs all attempts\n\n#### **internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go**\n- Package: `orchestrator`\n- Key type:\n  - `Orchestrator` - Main orchestration engine\n- Key methods:\n  - `New()` - Initializes sub-components (Docker, EC2, Scaler, SpotHandler) based on mode\n  - `Start()` - Runs poll loop on configurable interval\n  - `tick()` - Calls monitorRunning, dispatchPending, scaler.Evaluate\n  - `dispatchPending()` - Finds pending tasks, assigns to instances with capacity, starts containers\n  - `dispatch()` - Finds available instance, updates task to provisioning, runs container, tracks running count\n  - `findAvailableInstance()` - Finds running instance with available capacity\n  - `monitorRunning()` - Checks container status, detects timeouts, handles completions\n  - `handleCompletion()` - Processes container exit status, notifies, updates instance count\n  - `killTask()` - Stops container, marks task failed, updates instance count\n- **Features**:\n  - Max concurrent tasks calculated from auth mode + instance config\n  - Task timeout enforcement (MaxRuntimeMin)\n  - Inspect failure tracking with 3-failure threshold before kill\n  - Instance container count tracking\n  - Detailed webhook notifications on every state change\n\n#### **internal/orchestrator/docker.go**\n- Package: `orchestrator`\n- Key types:\n  - `ContainerStatus` (struct): Tracks container exit code, needs_input flag, error, log tail, PR URL\n  - `DockerManager` - Manages Docker operations via SSM or local shell\n- Key methods:\n  - `RunAgent()` - Builds docker run command with env vars (task params, auth, GitHub token, custom env vars)\n  - `InspectContainer()` - Checks state, reads `status.json` from container\n  - `StopContainer()` - Kills + removes container\n  - `GetLogs()` - Fetches container logs (tail-able)\n  - `runCommand()` - Routes to SSM or local exec\n  - `runLocalCommand()` - Uses bash exec for local mode\n  - `runSSMCommand()` - Uses AWS SSM SendCommand + waiter for EC2 mode\n- **Environment variables passed to container**:\n  - Task: TASK_ID, REPO_URL, BRANCH, TARGET_BRANCH, PROMPT, MODEL, EFFORT, MAX_BUDGET_USD, MAX_TURNS, CREATE_PR, SELF_REVIEW, PR_TITLE, PR_BODY, CLAUDE_MD, TASK_CONTEXT\n  - Auth: AUTH_MODE, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY (if api_key mode), CLAUDE_CREDENTIALS_PATH mount (if max_subscription mode)\n  - GitHub: GITHUB_TOKEN\n  - Custom env vars from task.EnvVars\n- Docker constraints: 1 CPU, 3GB RAM per container\n- Parses `status.json` written by entrypoint for detailed completion status\n\n#### **internal/orchestrator/ec2.go**\n- Package: `orchestrator`\n- Key type:\n  - `EC2Manager` - EC2 API wrapper\n- Key methods:\n  - `LaunchSpotInstance()` - Creates one-time spot instance\n    - Uses either launch template (preferred, provides AMI, instance type, tags, etc.) or AMI + instance type directly\n    - Spot termination behavior: terminate (not stop)\n  - `TerminateInstance()` - Stops EC2 instance\n  - `DescribeInstance()` - Fetches EC2 instance details\n- Lazy client initialization on first use\n\n#### **internal/orchestrator/scaler.go**\n- Package: `orchestrator`\n- Key interface:\n  - `scaler` - `Evaluate()`, `RequestScaleUp()` methods\n- Key type:\n  - `Scaler` - EC2 auto-scaling implementation\n- Key methods:\n  - `Evaluate()` - Calls reconcilePending, reconcileRunning, scaleDown\n  - `RequestScaleUp()` - Launches new instance if under MaxInstances and none pending\n  - `reconcilePending()` - Waits for pending instances to boot, checks SSM + Docker readiness before marking running\n  - `reconcileRunning()` - Detects externally terminated instances, marks draining\n  - `scaleDown()` - Terminates idle instances (5 min of no containers)\n  - `isSSMReady()` - Checks SSM agent ping status\n  - `isDockerReady()` - Verifies agent image is available\n- Idle timeout: 5 minutes\n\n#### **internal/orchestrator/local.go**\n- Package: `orchestrator`\n- Key type:\n  - `localScaler` - No-op scaler for local mode (empty implementations)\n\n#### **internal/orchestrator/spot.go**\n- Package: `orchestrator`\n- Key type:\n  - `SpotHandler` - Handles spot interruption events\n- Key methods:\n  - `CheckInterruptions()` - Polls running instances for termination state\n  - `isInterrupted()` - Checks EC2 state for shutting-down/terminated\n  - `handleInterruption()` - Marks instance draining, re-queues all running tasks back to pending with retry_count++\n- **Behavior**: Seamless re-queueing without losing work on spot interruptions\n\n#### **docker/Dockerfile**\n- Base: `node:20-slim`\n- Installs: git, curl, ca-certificates, build-essential, python3, python3-pip, jq, openssh-client, gh (GitHub CLI), @anthropic-ai/claude-code (npm)\n- User: non-root `agent` user\n- Git config: user \"backflow-agent\", email \"backflow-agent@noreply.github.com\", default branch \"main\"\n- Entrypoint: `/home/agent/entrypoint.sh`\n\n#### **docker/entrypoint.sh**\n- 334 lines, comprehensive agent lifecycle script\n- Key stages:\n  1. Clone repo with depth 50\n  2. Checkout target branch, create working branch\n  3. Inject CLAUDE.md if provided\n  4. Authenticate with GitHub if GITHUB_TOKEN set\n  5. Build full prompt with context + git instructions\n  6. Run Claude Code with retries (up to 3 attempts)\n  7. Parse stream-json output for completion/needs-input status\n  8. Extract PR URL if created\n  9. Commit agent output log to .backflow/ directory\n  10. Post prompt comment on PR\n  11. Self-review phase (optional, 20% of coding budget, min $2)\n  12. Write status.json for orchestrator\n- **Retry logic**: On failure, appends error to prompt for next attempt\n- **Self-review**: Uses separate Claude call with focused review prompt, posts findings as PR comment\n- **Output format**: stream-json (one JSON object per line)\n\n#### **Makefile**\nTargets:\n- `build` - Compile to bin/backflow\n- `run` - Build + run (sources .env)\n- `test` - go test ./... -v -count=1\n- `lint` - go vet ./...\n- `clean` - Remove bin/\n- `docker-build` - Multi-arch buildx (amd64+arm64)\n- `docker-build-local` - Single-arch\n- `docker-push` - Tag + push (requires REGISTRY=)\n- `docker-deploy` - Full pipeline: login, buildx, push\n- `db-status` - Dump SQLite state\n- `setup-aws` - Create AWS infrastructure\n- `deps` - go mod tidy\n\n#### **go.mod**\n- Module: `github.com/backflow-labs/backflow`\n- Go version: 1.24.1\n- Direct dependencies:\n  - aws-sdk-go-v2 (EC2, SSM, config)\n  - go-chi/chi/v5 (HTTP router)\n  - mattn/go-sqlite3 (SQLite driver)\n  - oklog/ulid/v2 (ULID generation)\n  - rs/zerolog (Structured logging)\n\n#### **Test Files**\n\n**internal/api/handlers_test.go**:\n- TestHealthCheck - Verifies health endpoint returns 200\n- TestCreateAndGetTask - Creates task via POST, retrieves via GET\n- TestListTasks - Tests listing with filters\n- Uses temporary SQLite database for isolation\n\n**internal/models/task_test.go**:\n- TestCreateTaskRequestValidation - Tests validation (valid input, missing fields, negative budget, effort validation)\n- TestTaskStatusIsTerminal - Tests all statuses against terminal/non-terminal\n\n**internal/store/sqlite_test.go**:\n- testStore helper - Creates temp DB with cleanup\n- TestTaskCRUD - Full cycle: create, get, update, list with filter, delete\n- Tests JSON serialization of arrays and maps\n- Tests timestamp handling\n\n#### **.env.example**\nComprehensive configuration template with all variables:\n- Auth: BACKFLOW_AUTH_MODE, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, CLAUDE_CREDENTIALS_PATH\n- Server: BACKFLOW_LISTEN_ADDR, BACKFLOW_DB_PATH\n- AWS: AWS_REGION, BACKFLOW_INSTANCE_TYPE, BACKFLOW_LAUNCH_TEMPLATE_ID, BACKFLOW_MAX_INSTANCES, BACKFLOW_CONTAINERS_PER_INSTANCE\n- Agent defaults: MODEL, EFFORT, MAX_BUDGET, MAX_RUNTIME_MIN, MAX_TURNS\n- Webhooks: BACKFLOW_WEBHOOK_URL, BACKFLOW_WEBHOOK_EVENTS\n- Orchestrator: BACKFLOW_POLL_INTERVAL_SEC\n\n#### **scripts/**\nAll scripts are bash with comprehensive error handling:\n\n- **build-agent-image.sh** - Multi-arch buildx to ECR\n- **create-task.sh** - CLI for submitting tasks (50+ lines), supports all task options via flags\n- **db-status.sh** - Shows task/instance status summaries\n- **setup-aws.sh** - One-time infrastructure setup\n- **user-data.sh** - EC2 bootstrap (install Docker, SSM agent, pull image)\n\n#### **docs/**\n\n- **file-reference.md** - 105 lines, complete and accurate documentation of all files\n- **schema.md** - 94 lines, detailed database schema with column descriptions, types, defaults, indexes, and status lifecycle diagrams\n\n### Summary of Codebase Size & Complexity\n\n- **Total Go files**: 16 (.go)\n- **Total test files**: 3 (_test.go)\n- **Total shell scripts**: 5\n- **Docker files**: 2 (Dockerfile + entrypoint.sh)\n- **Documentation files**: 2 (markdown)\n- **Configuration files**: 3 (go.mod, .env.example, .gitignore)\n\n### Key Patterns & Architecture\n\n1. **Interface-based design**: Store, Notifier, LogFetcher, scaler - all abstractions for testability\n2. **Polling architecture**: 5-second (configurable) tick loop instead of event-driven\n3. **Status tracking**: Both Task and Instance have explicit lifecycle states\n4. **Dual mode**: EC2 mode with spot instances or local Docker mode\n5. **Dual auth**: API key (multi-agent) or Max subscription (single-agent)\n6. **Container isolation**: 1 CPU, 3GB RAM per task\n7. **Retry logic**: Task retries on spot interruption, Claude retries up to 3 times on failure\n8. **Webhook notifications**: Event-driven async notifications with retry\n9. **Self-review**: Optional Claude-driven PR review after task completion\n10. **Log persistence**: Agent output saved to `.backflow/` directory in working branch\n\n### Comparison with Existing file-reference.md\n\nThe existing documentation is **accurate**. All 44 file descriptions in file-reference.md match the actual code. No updates needed.\n\nAll file paths are absolute paths as found in `/home/agent/workspace/`."}],"totalDurationMs":102799,"totalTokens":72951,"totalToolUseCount":31,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2134,"cache_read_input_tokens":65654,"output_tokens":5158,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2134},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
